<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talks Held With France on Security, Defense </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2301180694 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1000 GMT 23 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2301180694 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Riga today, Alain Lamassoure, minister delegate 
of European affairs at the French Foreign Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs, offered Latvia several proposals for tackling issues of 
national security. One of the proposals is joining Balladur's 
plan, or the European stability pact, the draft of which was 
worked out by the French premier. 
  This plan envisages joint discussion and tackling of various 
conflicts and problems between neighboring countries. It is 
planned in the draft to pay particular attention to problems 
which occur in relations between small countries and neighboring 
great powers. 
  France will also assist Latvia in joining the European 
Union. 
An agreement is currently being worked out between the European 
Union and Latvia, and France wishes that the agreement will also 
have a political significance and make it possible for Latvia to 
become a member state of the European Union in the future. 
  In addition, Lamassoure said that France supports the 
concept 
of Latvia joining the West European Union as an associate member. 
  The Partnership for Peace cooperation program offered by 
NATO 
would also help to tackle the issues of Latvian security. As 
Lamassoure said, an agreement is currently being prepared 
between Latvia and France on cooperation in defense issues. The 
agreement provides for training of Latvian military experts in 
France. Both countries have already coordinated all the 
political aspects of the agreement and it could be signed in the 
near future. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-57117 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov015_u_94003" </HT>


