in the framework of the Baltic summit there, said Pavlovskis. 
They started to shape a cooperation agreement of Latvian, 
Estonian and Lithuanian frontier services, the minister said. 
  The signature of the agreement is scheduled for February. 
The 
first results of this cooperation may be seen already in March, 
the defense minister said. 

