<H3> <TI>   Fedorov Says Collapse `Inevitable' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101152794 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1400 GMT 
21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2101152794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] No matter who is put in charge of the Finance 
Ministry, collapse is inevitable given the present mood of the 
government. This view was expressed to journalists by the former 
Finance Minister Boris Fedorov, who is a member of the State 
Duma. He said it would be best if one of his deputies were to 
be appointed acting minister. Fedorov believes that such a 
person would be able, within certain limits, to keep the ship on 
course. At the same time he disclosed that two or three of his 
deputies and several departmental heads intend to leave the 
Finance Ministry in the near future. 

</TEXT>

