<H3> <TI>   Vice Premier Yarov's Responsibilities Outlined </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2101140794 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 21 Jan 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2101140794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Untitled ITAR-TASS report] </F>
  [Text] By all accounts, Yuriy Yarov will retain the post 
of vice premier in the new government, Valeriy Vorontsov, the 
vice premier's adviser, has told ITAR-TASS. 
  He explained that Yuriy Yarov will continue to manage the 
social sphere for the government. Furthermore, he added, the 
vice premier will also be responsible for questions of the 
Cabinet's current work. Let us recall here that Yuriy Yarov is 
chairman of the Commission for the Burial of the Remains of the 
Tsar's Family and is also responsible for commemorating the date 
of the siege of Leningrad. However, the vice premier's adviser 
noted, the management of the Ministry of Health will in all 
likelihood be transferred to the control of First Vice Premier 
Oleg Soskovets. 

</TEXT>

