<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Denies Chernomyrdin Uses `Foreign Advisors' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101190294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1745 
GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2101190294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Perkina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 21 Jan -- "Throughout his term in office as 
leader of the Cabinet of Ministers, Viktor Chernomyrdin has not 
used the services of foreign advisors, and neither does he now", 
ITAR-TASS was told today by the head of the Russian Government's 
press service, Valentin Sergeyev. He had been asked about the 
reaction of the head of the government to a letter from 
economists Anders Oslund (Sweden) and Jeffrey Sachs (United 
States) in which they decline "to further assist the Russian 
Government". 
  According to Sergeyev, the head of the government believes 
that "the mechanical transfer of western economic methods to 
Russian soil has caused much more harm than good". 
  "The reform course drawn up by the Russian Government and 
approved by the president naturally incorporates some elements 
of Western market economics, but it primarily takes account of 
particular features of our state and people and of traditions in 
Russia", Valentin Sergeyev concluded. 

</TEXT>

