<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Filatov Outlines Presidential Administration Reform </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2201131994 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1000 GMT 
22 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2201131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The document on the reform of the presidential 
administration apparatus will probably be signed next week, 
Sergey Filatov reported to an ITAR-TASS correspondent. 
  According to Filatov, at the moment its work with the 
Federal 
Assembly needs to be intensified. In connection with this, a 
new structure is being set up to work in this area with factions 
and deputies' groups. Among other areas of the presidential 
administration's work in need of improvement, Filatov also 
mentioned the increase of the control functions over 
implementation of edicts and instructions issued by the 
president, improvement of the analytical service and relations 
with the media. As Filatov noted, the document stresses the 
important role to be played by the department engaged in working 
with the territories. In his opinion, the analysis of the 
pre-election campaign and elections has revealed various 
shortcomings in the work of local presidential representatives. 
As Filatov reported, in future, the candidates for the post of 
presidential representatives will have to be approved by heads 
of the local administration. 

</TEXT>

