<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Releases Defense, Security Adviser Volkogonov </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401110994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1030 
GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2401110994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 24 Jan (ITAR-TASS) -- Russian Federation 
President Boris Yeltsin signed a decree today releasing Dmitriy 
Volkogonov from the post of adviser. He was an adviser on 
defense and security matters and chairman of the president's 
commission investigating the disappearance without trace of 
foreign citizens and of Russian citizens missing in unexplained 
circumstances outside the borders of the former Soviet Union. 
The Russian Federation president's decision was made in 
connection with D. Volkogonov's election to the State Duma of 
the Federal Assembly, the Russian Federation president's press 
service reports. 

