<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Debates Military Reform </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2201031694 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0200 GMT 
22 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2201031694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Russian Defense Ministry has held an expanded 
interdepartmental conference to discuss a concept of 
military-legal reform for the Russian Armed Forces. 
  It was noted during the conference that the purposes, goals, 
and stages of a military-legal reform should fit the concept for 
the structure of the country's armed forces and the principles 
of a democratic, law-based state. Therefore, they will be drawn 
up in accordance with the Constitution and the Russian military 
doctrine. It is planned to complete the drafting of a concept 
for military-legal reform in June 1994. 

</TEXT>

