<H3> <TI>   Conference on Defense Industry Conversion Begins </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401100594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0830 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2401100594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Ostanin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 24 TASS -- The Russian Government 
Academy is holding an international conference to discuss the 
defence industry's conversion to civilian production in the 
Russian Federation and other countries of the Commonwealth of 
Independent States. 
  The conference was convened on the initiative of the non- 
governmental foundation "International Humanitarian Dimension", 
the Russian Government Academy, the conversion fund attached to 
the presidium of the Russian Academy of Sciences and some 
research and producing associations of the Russian Federation. 
  Representatives of the Federal Defence Ministry, scientists, 
researchers and Russian and foreign business people are taking 
part in the plenary session of the conference. 
  Its main aim is to establish horizontal links between 
investors and manufacturers of new products, as well as the 
centres for the creation of new jobs for former servicemen and 
their families. 
  The three-day conference will also discuss political aspects 
of conversion, the role of information in the development of 
businesses in Russia and other CIS countries. 

</TEXT>

