<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commentary on Reports of Submarine Sales to DPRK </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2501023894 Moscow Radio Moscow in Mandarin 1000 GMT 24 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2501023894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Moscow </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Commentary by Surikov from the "Current Event and </F>
Commentary" program] 
  [Text] Listeners: The Western mass media reported over 
the weekend that Russia is arming Korea [DPRK] and has sold 40 
submarines to them. What is the true story? Here is a 
commentary by station commentator Surikov. 
  First of all, it should be noted that arms sales are now one 
of the major export items of many countries. Commercial arms 
supplies should not be a cause for surprise. Russia's submarine 
sales to Korea are nothing but scrap metal. The intermediary in 
this purely commercial deal is a Japanese company. The 
company's general manager (Shibata) told ITAR-TASS NEWS AGENCY: 
Last October Russia sold three submarines, which had long been 
decommissioned and scrapped, to Korea. The submarines carried 
no weapons whatsoever. Pyongyang cannot use them for training, 
much less for combat. The most reliable guarantee is that 
representatives from the Russian Navy directly oversaw 
professional Korean workers in breaking down the submarines into 
several parts. The Japanese company did not violate domestic 
laws banning indirect weapons and military technology sales to 
other countries. 
  Speaking at a press conference in Vladivostok, General 
Gromov, commander in chief of the Russian Navy, said: Russia 
has not supplied weapons to Pyongyang; nor does it plan to do so 
(?in the near future). Selling scrap metal to other countries 
is not a secret practice. Many scrapped and disarmed warships 
and submarines are berthed in some Russian ports. (Shibata) 
said: Korea aside, China and Japan are very interested in 
buying such scrap metal. This shows that reports by the Western 
mass media are only rumors that do not tally with the facts at 
all. 

</TEXT>

