<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bilateral Relations Discussed With Uzbek Delegation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101154994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1432 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2101154994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Georgiy Shmelyov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 21 TASS -- Russian and Uzbek 
delegations held a working meeting at the Russian Foreign 
Ministry on Friday to discuss bilateral relations, the situation 
of ethnic Russians in Uzbekistan and some regional problems. 
  The Russian delegation was headed by Russian Foreign 
Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev and the Uzbek delegation, led by Uzbek Parliament 
Acting Chairman Erkin Khalilov, included Kozyrev's counterpart 
Saidmukhtar Said Asymov. 
  Vladimir Shumeyko, chairman of the upper chamber of the 
Russian Parliament, took part in the talks, which were held in a 
friendly and constructive atmosphere. "We met as real friends, 
partners and close neighbours. Our relations are notable for a 
full mutual understanding and close interaction", Kozyrev said. 
  Khalilov seconded this view by saying the two delegations 
should not sit on two opposing sides of the table but at a round 
table with no division between them. 
  In the course of the talks, a decision was reached to 
establish a mixed group of Russian and Uzbek experts to draft 
legislative proposals on citizenship. 
  Kozyrev's political advisor Galina Sidorova told ITAR-TASS 
the negotiations were business-like and its results will lead to 
a practical settlement of problems and mutually acceptable 
decisions. 

</TEXT>

