<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Meets With Tatar, Mari Presidents </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101135394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1221 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2101135394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By unidentified ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 21 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin held a meeting with Tatarstan's President Mintimer 
Shaymiyev in the Kremlin on Friday. Development and legal 
foundations of relations between the republics were the main 
theme of the conversation. The need to speed up the drafting 
and signing of an agreement on the separation of powers was 
noted. Negotiations on this matter will shortly be resumed. 
  On the same day Yeltsin met with President of Mari Republic 
Vladislav Zotin and Chairman of the State Assembly of the 
Republic Anatoliy Smirnov. The participants on the meeting told 
the Russian president about the political situation in the 
republic after the adoption of a new constitution. Economic and 
social problems, specifically problems of regulating the 
population's employment arising during the conversion of the 
military-industrial complex were discussed, the presidential 
press office noted. 

</TEXT>

