<F P=100> BALTIC STATES </F>
<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meri Receives French European Affairs Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101105694 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1000 
GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2101105694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Estonian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Alain Lamassoure, French minister [delegate] for 
European affairs, is currently on a visit to Estonia. He held a 
meeting with Estonian President Lennart Meri today. One of the 
key aims of Lamassoure's visit is to make preparations for the 
European stability pact's opening conference in the Baltic 
states. For Estonia, the main political importance of the 
European stability pact--or the so-called Balladur 
initiative--comes from the fact that the pact views the Baltic 
states as possible European Union members for the first time. 
  Lamassoure will be leaving Estonia at noon today. He will 
travel on to Latvia and Lithuania. 

</TEXT>

