  [Text] Moscow January 24 ITAR-TASS -- Aleksandr Yakovlev 
from the Institute of State and Law of the Russian Academy of 
Sciences was appointed by President Boris Yeltsin as his 
representative in parliament, the press service of the Russian 
leader said on Monday. 
  Yakovlev was born in 1927 and is doctor of law. 
  Aleksandr Maksimovich Yakovlev is not to be confused with 
Aleksandr Nikolayevich Yakovlev who had been appointed by the 
president as head of the "Ostankino" TV network. 

