<H3> <TI>   Russian Border Guards Attacked on Afghan Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2201170794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1353 GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2201170794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russian border guards were fired on from guns and 
rocket installations several times throughout Friday at the Turg 
height near the 12 and 13 outposts of Moscow's Border Unit on 
the Tajik-Afghan frontier. The enemy gunners were suppressed by 
counter fire. No Russian serviceman was hurt. 
  As an army officer in Dushanbe has told Interfax, the height 
has been continuously shelled for the second day from Tajikistan 
by small groups of infiltrators from Afghanistan. 
  The spokesman reported that two Tajiks were detained when 
they tried to cross into Afghanistan in the Ishkashim area of 
the Gorno-Badakhshan region on Thursday night [20 January]. 
They were unarmed. 

</TEXT>

