<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Azerbaijani Warplane Shot Down in Karabakh </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2401160694 Yerevan ARMENPRES International Service in 
Armenian 1211 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2401160694 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARMENPRES International Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, 24 Jan (ARMENPRES)--The Nagorno-Karabakh 
Republic [NKR] Defense Army's Air Defense Forces shot down one 
of two Azerbaijani warplanes trying to bomb Stepanakert not far 
from the NKR's capital on 22 January. The pilot's fate is not 
known. 
  In recent days, the enemy has actively used air force all 
along the war front. 
  Yesterday, NKR Defense Army units halted Azerbaijani 
offensives in the direction of Mardakert, Agdam-Askeran, and 
Gadrut-Fizuli. Two Karabakh fighters died and six were wounded. 
The enemy lost 33 men. 
  Karabakh positions have been coming under artillery and 
rocket shelling on the borders of Agdamskiy and Mardakertskiy 
Rayons since morning. 

</TEXT>

