<H3> <TI>   Landyk: Nation Ready To Join CIS Economic Union </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2501080294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0754 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2501080294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Andrey Varlamov] </F>
  [Text] Tokyo January 25 TASS -- Ukraine plans to announce 
at the regular CIS summit this March its decision to accede 
fully to the economic union of the Commonwealth of Independent 
States (CIS), Ukrainian Vice-Premier Valentin Landyk told the 
Japanese newspaper "NIHON KEIZAI". His interview is published 
in today's issue of the daily. 
  "The Ukrainian leader," the newspaper says, quoting his 
pronouncements, "has stressed that his republic should rely 
primarily on relations with the states of the former Soviet 
Union and the East European nations in order to improve the 
economic situation in the country. 
  "To make the CIS economic union function effectively," 
Landyk 
believes, "it is necessary, first and foremost, to create a 
system for mutual settlements, based on a specialised 
inter-state bank." 

</TEXT>

