<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ambassador Discusses Involvement in FRY Sanctions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2201105994 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 0800 GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2201105994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, 21 Jan -- Volodymyr Vasylenko, Ukraine's 
ambassador to the Benelux countries, met Ambassador Napolitano 
[name as received], coordinator of EC/CSCE sanctions against the 
Federal Republic of Yugoslavia. The sides discussed a wide 
range of issues connected to Ukraine's participation in 
implementing UN sanctions against Yugoslavia. Individual 
attention was paid to cooperation by the customs and border 
services of Ukraine with the authorities of Danube countries and 
with the missions for facilitating sanctions in these countries, 
and to the possibilities of rendering financial and technical 
assistance to Ukraine, which is needed for efficiently securing 
the sanctions regime. 
  The Ukrainian ambassador drew Napolitano's attention to the 
necessity of stepping up the search for practical ways of 
compensating losses experienced by third countries, including 
our state, as a result of introducing sanctions against 
Yugoslavia. 

</TEXT>

