<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Law Specifies Punishment for Crimes Against State </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2401134094 Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 21 Jan 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> AU2401134094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Ukraine's Law on Intensifying Criminal Responsibility for </F>
Some Crimes Against the State" issued in Kiev on 24 Dec 93] 
  [Text] In order to intensify the protection of the 
constitutional system and territorial integrity of Ukraine, as 
well as public security, Ukraine's Supreme Council resolves as 
follows: 
  Articles 56-1, 62, and 71 will read as follows: 
  "Article 56-1. Actions aimed at changing by force or 
overthrowing the constitutional system or seizing state power, 
as well as conspiracy to commit such actions -- 
  "are punishable by imprisonment of between five and 15 years 
with confiscation of property. 
  "Public calls for changing the state power by force or 
overthrowing state power, as well as dissemination of materials 
calling for such actions -- 
  "are punishable by five years' imprisonment or a fine of up 
to 100 times the minimum wage. 
  "Actions specified by Part 2 of this article that are 
committed by a representative of power, repeated, or committed 
by a group of people as a conspiracy -- 
  "are punishable by imprisonment of between three and eight 
years"; 
  "Article 62. Encroachment upon Ukraine's territorial 
integrity: 
  "Deliberate actions committed for the purpose of changing 
the 
territory or state borders of Ukraine in violation of the 
procedure established by the Ukrainian Constitution, as well as 
public calls or dissemination of materials with calls to commit 
such actions -- 
  "are publishable by imprisonment of up to five years. 
  "The same actions, if committed by a representative of power 
or by a group of people as a conspiracy, or if they involve 
incitement of ethnic or regilious hostility -- 
  "are punishable by imprisonment of between three and 10 
years. 
  "Actions specified by parts 1 and 2 of this article that 
have 
resulted in loss of life or other grave consequences -- 
  "are punishable by imprisonment of between 10 and 15 years"; 
  "Article 71. Mass disorders: 
  "The organization of state disorders, which involve violence 
against the individual, pogroms, arson, destruction of property, 
resistance to representatives of power with the use of weapons 
or other objects used as weapons, or active participation in 
mass disorders -- 
  "is punishable by imprisonment of between two and 12 years. 
  "Such actions that result in loss of life or other grave 
consequences -- 
  "are punishable by imprisonment of between 10 and 15 years." 
  [Signed] Ukrainian President L. Kravchuk [as published, laws 
are usually issued by the Supreme Council and signed by its 
chairman Ivan Plyushch] 
  [Dated]Kiev, 24 December 1993 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
