<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Leads Exercise of Power Ministries </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401204994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1825 
GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2401204994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By UKRINFORM-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Kiev, 24 Jan -- The first strategic exercise which 
started today under the leadership of the supreme commander of 
the Ukraine Armed Forces, President Leonid Kravchuk, is called 
upon to resolve the tasks of territorial defense. 
  Its aim, the press service of the Ukraine military 
department 
announced, is to work out the interaction between the ministries 
of defense, internal affairs, the security service, the National 
Guard, border troops and the civilian defense of Ukraine. 
  Leonid Kravchuk drew the attention of the leaders of the 
power ministries to the importance of such an exercise, and 
directed them to fulfill with quality the tasks set and to the 
need to give an objective appraisal of the work done. 
  Under the plan for conducting the exercise, the press 
service 
of the Ukraine Ministry of Defense notes, the use of troops is 
not envisaged. 

