<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reformer Group Holds Conference in Kharkov </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101232494 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 2115 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2101232494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kharkov -- On 21 January, the first all-Ukrainian 
conference of the Interregional Bloc of Reforms began its work 
in Kharkov. Taking part in it are more than 600 representatives 
of the regional organizations of political parties and 
movements, entrepreneurial and industrial structures, 
foundations and public organizations from Odessa, Poltava, Sumy, 
Dnepropetrovsk, Zaporozhye, Zhytomir, Nikolayev, Kiev, and other 
cities of Ukraine. One of the co-chairmen of the bloc, 
Volodymyr Hrynyov, people's deputy of Ukraine and chairman of 
the "Nova Ukrayina" [New Ukraine] association, emphasized that 
the goal of the future strong parliamentary coalition, which the 
bloc expects to reach at the March election to the Supreme 
Council, should be order and the market in Ukraine. He believes 
that ways toward this lie in privatization, improvement of the 
financial system, establishment of equal economic relations with 
Russia, changes within the authority institutions, and the 
priorities of the private sector. The conference is planned to 
approve an appeal of the Hrynyov-Kuchma bloc to the citizens of 
Ukraine on the election eve and a "Declaration on the goals and 
principles of the activity of the Interregional bloc of 
reforms." The four fundamental provisions of the 
"Declaration..." envision the following: priority of human 
rights and freedoms, creation of a civilized market society in 
Ukraine on the principles of private ownership of land and the 
means of production, refusal from any attempts to build a state 
with national and ethnic priorities, refusal of the policy of 
confrontation with Russia and other CIS countries. Also, the 
conference delegates will take part in the work of the "Kharkov 
Business Assembly." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

