<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Approves Plan for Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401191694 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1350 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2401191694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kharkov -- On 22 January the all-Ukrainian 
conference of the Interregional reform bloc (the Hrynyov-Kuchma 
bloc) ended with a meeting of the Kharkov business assembly. 
The conference approved a program of actions "Ukraine's path 
toward economic revival, a civil society and civilized state," a 
declaration about the aims and principles of the bloc's activity 
and an appeal to Ukraine's citizens. At the basis of these 
documents lies the assertion of the indisputability of immediate 
economic reforms in Ukraine and of normalizing economic 
relations with Russia and other CIS countries. At the next 
conference which is planned for the end of February in 
Dnepropetrovsk, there will be a gathering of parliamentary 
candidates who have been nominated and supported by the bloc. 
  At a news conference after the end of the assembly, people's 
deputy and co-founder of the bloc Volodymyr Hrynyov, stressed: 
Democratic and centrist forces do not have the right to lose the 
upcoming elections; young and energetic political leaders from 
the regions where, in his opinion, the state's new economic 
policy will be formed, should be elected to the new parliament. 

</TEXT>

