<H3> <TI>   Dniester Republic Reintroduces `Old Rubles' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401223394 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 2000 GMT 
24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2401223394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Dniester Republic reintroduced old rubles today, 
with a stamp depicting Aleksandr Suvorov glued on them. Locals 
have christened them suvorovki. Pensioners were first to get 
the new money. The minimum pension is equal to 60,000 stamped 
rubles, which is enough for about five kilos of boiled sausage. 

</TEXT>

