<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Members Temporarily Dismissed To Run in Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2401083194 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1800 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2401083194 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 21/1/1994 -- 9 out of 32 members 
of Moldovan Government were temporarily dismissed for the period 
of electoral campaign according to the presidential decree, 
stated to BASA Ion Sofronie, government press secretary. Here 
is the list of people on temporary dismissal: Andrei Sangheli, 
Moldovan premier (candidate of Moldovan Agrarian Democratic 
Party-PDAM); Nicolae Oleinic, vice premier (PDAM); Valentin 
Cunev, vice premier (PDAM); Vitalie Gorincioi, minister of 
agriculture and food (PDAM); Gheorghe Ghidirim, minister of 
health (Democratic Party of Labour); Petru Sandulache, minister 
of youth, sport and tourism (Reform Party); Visarion Cesuev, 
head of State Department for Privatization (Social-Democratic 
Party); Ion Ciocanu, head of Department of Languages (National 
Christian Party). Ion Ungureanu, minister of culture, also 
requested temporary dismissal in case of his registration as an 
independent candidate. Sofronie added that Premier Sangheli 
could execute his power in exceptional situations. His last 
execution of power was due to the emergency state decreed in the 
Dniester region. 

</TEXT>

