<F P=100> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Arrives on Working Visit, Met by Akayev </TI></H3>
<H4>   To Discuss Bilateral Relations </H4>
<F P=102> LD2401215694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2142 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2401215694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Georgy Shmelev] </F>
  [Text] Bishkek January 25 TASS -- Russian Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev arrived in Bishkek on a working visit early on 
Tuesday [25 January]. 
  At Bishkek airport Kozyrev was met by Kyrgyz President Askar 
Akayev, Prime Minister Tursunbek Chyngyshev and other officials. 
This is the first foreign trip by the Russian foreign minister 
in 1994. 
  In an interview with ITAR-TASS Kozyrev said that he has 
delivered a personal message to Akayev from President Boris 
Yeltsin in which he confirmed Russia's readiness to provide 
assistance to Kyrgyzstan to further its reform. 
  In Bishkek Kozyrev is expected to meet with Kyrgyz leaders 
to 
discuss a wide range of issues concerning bilateral relations 
between the two countries, prospects for the development of the 
Commonwealth of Independent states and some aspects of regional 
and international cooperation. 
  From Bishkek Kozyrev will fly to Blagoveshchensk, 
administrative centre of the Amur region in the Russian Far 
East, and then further to China where he will arrive on an 
official visit later this week. 

</TEXT>

