<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Local Forces, Afghan Mojahedin Clash 23 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401142494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1331 
GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2401142494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe, 24 Jan -- An armed clash between a local 
self-defense detachment and a group of about 15 Afghan mojahedin 
who penetrated from the territory of adjacent Afghanistan, took 
place on 23 January in the region of the Tajik border village of 
Yamkun. After losing two men killed and several wounded the 
mojahedin retreated. During the battle the local population 
liberated two fellow villagers seized by the Afghans. 
  The authorities of Gorno-Badakhshan and representatives of 
the headquarters of the command of the Russian border troops in 
Tajikistan protested to the Afghan side and demanded that the 
organizers of this provocation are brought to justice. 
  The press center of the Russian border troops' command in 
Tajikistan reports that the situation in other sections along 
the Tajikistan-Afghanistan border remains complicated, but under 
control. According to the same source, no armed incidents in 
the Moskovskiy, Pyandzhskiy and other sections of the border 
have been registered in the last two days. 

</TEXT>

