<H3> <TI>   CIS Interpol Branches Hold Conference in Baku </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2401222194 Baku TURAN in English 2131 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2401222194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku (January 24) TURAN--A seminar of CIS national 
departments of Interpol took place in Baku during January 15-17, 
chief of Azeri National Bureau of Interpol Captain Tofik 
Murshudlu told TURAN news agency. 
  Representatives of national bureaus of Interpol from nine 
CIS 
states participated at the seminar. Representatives of 
Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Tajikistan and Turkmenistan could not 
take part in the seminar for technical matters. Armenian 
representatives did not participate at Baku seminar as well, 
though they sent their proposals to the organization committee 
of the forum. Baltic Interpol departments were presented by the 
chief of Latvian Interpol Department. 
  A resolution on the results of the seminar is adopted. The 
resolution states the necessity of development of the work on 
bringing the laws in the former USSR republics in conformity 
with the international norms, working out principals of 
cooperation and interconnection in the struggle against crime 
and narcotic drugs smuggling. The importance of improvement the 
communication means and exchange of information is also stressed. 

</TEXT>

