<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bill To Discharge Army Commander Submitted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2401205894 Tallinn ETA NEWS RELEASE in English 1758 GMT 24 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2401205894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA NEWS RELEASE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An Estonian parliament MP on Monday presented the 
Riigikogu [parliament] a bill on discharging Major General 
Aleksander Einseln, the head of the Estonian army. 
  Katrin Linde said in her statement that according to 
statutes 
of the headquarters of the Estonian Defence Forces, the head of 
the headquarters must also be head of the army. 
  The head of the headquarters is Colonel Ants Laaneots. 
  Nugis, the speaker of the Riigikogu, said the bill 
contradicted the constitution. 
  Linde claimed that according to the law regulating military 
service of Estonian officers, any officer older than 60 must be 
discharged from armed forces. Einseln is 63. Linde also said 
that according to the same law, no officer could be granted 
higher military rank than he had had while serving in a foreign 
army. 
  Estonian Riigikogu on May 4 last year adopted a bill making 
retired U.S. Colonel Einseln head of the Estonian army. 
President Lennart Meri later made him Major General. 

</TEXT>

