<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official: Country Charted by European Standards </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2001210894 Tallinn ETA NEWS RELEASE in English 1849 GMT 20 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2001210894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA NEWS RELEASE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, January 20 -- According to a cooperation 
programme between Estonia and Sweden, concluded in September 
last year, Estonian Chart Centre will finish work on a complete 
and thorough up-to-date Estonian map, based on satellite photos, 
by the end of 1995, Heiki Potter of the State Land Board told 
ETA. 
  The final cost of the project is 11 million Estonian kroons 
(about 785,714 USD), 85 percent of which will be financed by 
Sweden. 
  According to an agreement between the Estonian Land Board 
and 
Swedish Satellitbild corporation, Sweden will be responsible for 
the satellite photos, digital data basis and necessary equipment 
to decode and interpret the data. The new system will allow 
continuous renewal of the basic map, survey of environmental 
situation and of how natural resources are used in Estonia. 
1,000 maps will be printed at the beginning for the use of 
state and municipality institutions. 

</TEXT>

