<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Abkhaz Organization Protests Russian Troops </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401212694 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 1900 
GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2401212694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The heads of Abkhazia's liberation organization held 
a press conference in Tbilisi. The chairman of the organization, 
Boris Kakubava, member of the Georgian parliament; the political 
secretary, Malkhaz Pataraia; and Abkhazia's military commissar, 
Vakhtang Vekua, answered journalists' questions. 
  Boris Kakubava blamed the government because for four 
months, 
since handing over Abkhazia, it had done nothing for the return 
to Abkhazia, in the same way as we were evicted from there. 
  They criticized sharply the Geneva talks. We are not against 
talks, said Kakubava, but we must have a reserve of permanent 
armed forces and must not allow the Russian troops under the 
auspices of the UN into Abkhazia. 
  The members of the organization expressed the wish that as 
of 
now, representatives of the evicted population of Abkhazia 
participate in talks on settling the conflict. They protested 
against the return of refugees in the Gali rayon and justified 
their protest by the fact that it was being conducted under the 
jurisdiction of the [Abkhaz] separatists and that the civilians 
would have no security guarantees. Our only aim is to return to 
Abkhazia, said Boris Kakubava, and every lost day makes it 
unlikely. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

