<H3> <TI>   Agrarian Party of Georgia Founded </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901211694 Tbilisi CONTACT INFORMATION AGENCY in Russian 
1629 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1901211694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi CONTACT INFORMATION AGENCY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In connection with a great festival of the Orthodox 
world, Epiphany, and to overcome the most serious political and 
economic crisis in Georgia, the unification of all parties and 
political movements representing agriculture in the republic 
happened today. They were joined by a number of members of the 
Democratic Party and the societies Lemi and Mamuli [Homeland]. 
  A unified Agrarian Party of Georgia was founded. The head of 
the Agrarian Commission of the Georgian Parliament and an 
agricultural sciences doctor, Roin Liparteliani, was unanimously 
elected party chairman. 

