<H3> <TI>   Slezevicius Meets Swedish Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401193594 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 
1700 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2401193594 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lithuanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Adolfas Slezevicius, the prime minister of the 
Republic of Lithuania, met Carl Bildt, the prime minister of 
Sweden, in Stockholm today. The talks lasted for an hour and a 
half. Bilateral regional problems were discussed. The plan 
Partnership for Peace, security problems of the Baltic Sea 
region, the possibilities for the development of cooperation 
between Lithuania and Sweden, and economic relations between the 
two countries were discussed by the two prime ministers. 
  Kazys Bobelis, chairman of the Seimas Foreign Affairs 
Committee, Deputy Foreign Minister Algimantas Januska, Romualdas 
Kalonaitis, Lithuanian ambassador extraordinary and 
plenipotentiary in Sweden, Lars-Aake (Nilsson), state secretary 
at the Swedish Foreign Affairs, Ministry, Tom Werterman, head of 
the CSCE Sector at the Swedish Foreign Affairs Ministry 
Political Department, Lars Magnuson, Swedish ambassador 
extraordinary and plenipotentiary to Lithuania, and Jonas [name 
indistinct], Carl Bildt's adviser on international relations, 
were also present at the meeting. 

</TEXT>

