<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Envoy Presents Letter on EU Cooperation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2001105494 Vilnius ELTA NEWS BULLETIN in English 2124 GMT 
19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2001105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius ELTA NEWS BULLETIN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From ELTA "NEWS BULLETIN" No. 419] </F>
  [Text] Vilnius, 19 Jan -- A letter by Lithuanian Foreign 
Minister Povilas Gylys was handed over to Greek Foreign Minister 
Karolos Papoulias by Lithuanian Deputy Foreign Minister Albinas 
Januska visiting Greece. 
  Gylys stated in the letter that Lithuania called to start 
the 
negotiations on the associative agreement with the European 
Union [EU]. 
  It is noted in the letter that the dynamic development of 
economic and political situation in Eastern and Central Europe 
increases the necessity to create effective forms of integration 
into the European Union for the Baltic States. 
  Lithuania expressed its wish that the future free trade 
agreement with EU should comply with the commercial part of the 
associative agreement. 
  Gylys urged the Council of Europe to adopt the decision 
which 
would allow to transform the free trade agreement between EU and 
Lithuania into the associative agreement. 
  Greece presides in the Council of Europe during the first 
half of the year. 

</TEXT>

