<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Federation Council Supports Changed Economic Reform Course </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401145294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1410 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2401145294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksey Subbotin] </F>
  [Text] Ulan Ude January 24 TASS--"The Federation Council 
supports the correction of the course of economic reform," 
Leonid Potapov, Buryatia's parliament chairman who is also a 
member of the Federation Council, told a news conference in Ulan 
Ude on Monday [24 January]. 
  Potapov believes that "revolutionary romanticism, liberalism 
and monetarism should give way to the processes of state 
regulation during the transition to a market economy, while 
personnel changes in the government should correct the course of 
economic reform to bring it in line with the existing 
monopolised economy." 
  He stressed that "pragmatists in the new government can find 
specialists who will be able to move reforms from `the worst to 
the best' and expand the social basis of reform." 
  At the same time, he pointed to the importance of the 
constructive opposition to the government on the part of 
"supporters of radical economic approaches who have resigned." 

</TEXT>

