<H3> <TI>   Duma Deputy Kovalev Named Human Rights Representative </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401163794 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1500 GMT 
24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2401163794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sergey Kovalev, a State Duma deputy and well-known 
campaigner, has been appointed a plenipotentiary representative 
on human rights, Radio Moscow International has reported. 
Similar institutions of parliamentary missionaries exist in 
many democratic countries, but it is the first such institution 
in Russia. The main aim of the new institution is to monitor 
the work of government offices with the aim of out-of-court 
protection of human rights, [word indistinct] following up 
specific complaints made by citizens. 

</TEXT>

