<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Visits Agricultural Enterprises </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401201594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1833 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2401201594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Yuriy Likhopek and Serafim </F>
Bykhun] 
  [Text] Orel January 24 TASS--Russian Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin visited several agricultural enterprises in the 
Orel region, central Russia, on Monday [24 January]. 
  Chernomyrdin is in Orel to attend an agricultural conference 
opening here on Tuesday. The conference will discuss measures 
to ensure fuller use of the agroindustrial complex in central 
Russia and better food supplies to the country as a whole. 
  The conference, which will be attended by the leaders of the 
federal bodies of power and administration heads of 18 central 
Russian regions and their deputies in charge of agriculture, is 
expected to hear the prime minister's first statement on 
agricultural policy after recent reshuffles in the government. 
Informed sources told ITAR-TASS that the conference is expected 
to result in a government resolution on working out a programme 
for the development of the agroindustrial complexes of the 
central Russian regions for the period up to the year 2000. 
  Today conference participants visited some agricultural 
enterprises in the Orel region and food-processing factories. 
They also had conversations with private farmers. 
  Cherrnomyrdin was accompanied in his trip by Vice-Prime 
Minister Aleksandr Zaveryukha, Central Bank chairman Viktor 
Gerashchenko and Orel regional administration head Yegor Stroyev. 

</TEXT>

