<H3> <TI>   Cooperation Accord Signed With Uzbek Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2501121294 Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 22 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU2501121294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "A Cooperation Agreement Has Been </F>
Reached"] 
  [Text] Lieutenant General Rustam Akhmetov, minister of 
defense of the Republic of Uzbekistan, arrived in Ukraine on an 
official visit. He met with Ukraine's Minister of Defense Army 
General Vitaliy Radetskyy. In the course of the meeting, the 
leaders of the military departments exchanged experience in 
building armed forces and discussed questions of cooperation 
between the military structures of Ukraine and Uzbekistan. As 
reported by the Press Service of Ukraine's Ministry of Defense, 
particular attention was given to cooperation in the branches of 
rear and technical services, air defense, the training of 
officers' personnel, and so on. 
  The leaders of the military departments of the two states 
signed an agreement on military cooperation between the 
ministries of defense of Ukraine and the Republic of Uzbekistan. 

</TEXT>

