<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Discusses Trade, Travel Restrictions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601095094 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2601095094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev, speaking in 
Blagoveshchensk at a conference of representatives of regions of 
the Russian Far East bordering on China, said that the volume of 
bilateral trade in 1993 was $2.5 billion, with which it is 
possible to ease the shortage of consumer goods in Russia. 
Kozyrev also said that an agreement would come into force in 
1994 restricting visa-free entry into Russia for citizens of the 
PRC. Visa-free entry will only remain for holders of diplomatic 
or business passports. According to the minister, this is not a 
case of the recreation of an iron curtain. It is, nonetheless, 
necessary to know how many Chinese citizens are on Russian 
territory, Interfax reports. 

</TEXT>

