<F P=102>  PM2501152394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 25 Jan 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2501152394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA/ITAR-TASS report under the "Yesterday, </F>
Today, Tomorrow" rubric: "Supplies to Moscow Threatened With 
Disruption"] 
  [Text] The tense situation in the capital's economy has 
forced Moscow Mayor Yuriy Luzhkov to cut short his vacation. He 
had flown to Orel together with Viktor Chernomyrdin. The reason 
for the economic problems is that the Russian Government has 
built up a debt of approximately 250 billion rubles with various 
Moscow organizations and enterprises over the past year. 
  The supply of vital foodstuffs, goods, and services to 
Muscovites is threatened with disruption. 

</TEXT>

