<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Appoints Heads in Maritime Kray, Ryazan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2501140694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1334 
GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2501140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 25 Jan -- President of the Russian 
Federation Boris Yeltsin has signed an edict appointing Vladimir 
Ignatenko presidential representative in Maritime Kray. This 
was reported by the Russian presidential press service today. 
  On the nomination of the chairman of the Russian Government, 
Boris Yeltsin has appointed by edict Gennadiy Merkulov to the 
post of head of administration for Ryazan Oblast. 
  At the same time the Russian president signed an edict 
removing Lev Bashmakov from the post of head of administration 
for Ryazan Oblast. Lev Bashmakov was removed from his post on 
representations from the chairman of the Russian government for 
systematically exceeding his powers, failing to ensure 
implementation of the edicts of the Russian president aimed at 
building a market economy, and also for taking decisions which 
contribute to the destabilization of the political situation in 
the country. 

</TEXT>

