Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, 25 Jan (ARMENPRES)--Things are extremely 
tense in the Karabakh conflict zone. The Azerbaijani troops 
resumed their offensive against Mardakert this morning, but the 
Karabakh Army is halting the enemy attacks. An Azerbaijani tank 
was hit by 1030. 
  Active combat operations are taking place in the northwest 
of 
the war front. The enemy's army is trying to move deep into 
Mardakertskiy and Kelbadzharskiy Rayons. Again, the attack is 
being checked. 
  The Nagorno-Karabakh Republic Defense Army Press Service has 
denied an Azerbaijani Defense Ministry statement that claimed 
the Azerbaijani Army was successfully moving deep into 
Kelbadzharskiy Rayon and that the Armenians have suffered 
