<H3> <TI>   Iranian Bank To Open Branch; Forged Money Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2501155994 Yerevan ARMENPRES International Service in 
Armenian 1330 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2501155994 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARMENPRES International Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, 25 Jan (ARMENPRES)--Bagrat Asaturyan, 
president of the Armenian Central Bank, told reporters that the 
Armenian coins known as lumas will be brought to the Republic. 
The absence of the luma is creating major problems, mostly in 
retail trade, and is causing artificial inflation in the price 
of some goods. 
  Asaturyan also said that Iran's "Mellath" Bank will be the 
first foreign bank to start operating in Armenia soon. The 
building to be allocated to the bank in Republic Square is not 
ready. The Armenian side is doing everything to enable the bank 
to start operating as soon as possible. 
  The Armenian Central Bank reported a noticeable flow of 
forged Russian rubles and dollars from Russia to Armenia. 
Circulation is helped by the existence of a foreign currency 
"black market." 

</TEXT>

