<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Azeris `Successfully Advancing' on Kelbadzhar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2501143994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1414 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2501143994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Sevindj Abdullaeva and Viktor </F>
Shulman] 
  [Text] Baku January 25 TASS -- Azeri troops are 
successfully advancing towards the south-western town of 
Kelbadzhar, earlier captured by Armenians, the Defence Ministry 
of Azerbaijan reported on Tuesday. Kelbadzhar is still being 
controlled by Armenians in spite of their heavy losses in recent 
combat operations. 
  The ministry experts associate the desperate attempts of the 
Armenian troops to keep control over Kelbadzhar with the 
existence of gold mines in the region. 
  According to the source, "in the past few days the enemy has 
brought into action even badly trained recruits" in a bid to 
hold the positions. 
  The Azeri military say that as a result of their latest 
military success, the Armenian troops near the town of Agderi 
were cut off from supplies from Armenia. 
  On Monday Azeri troops surrounded and completely destroyed a 
group of 240 Armenian servicemen who tried to penetrate the 
combat zone from Armenia, the source added. 

</TEXT>

