<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze Seeks Tighter Government Management </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2501193794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1744 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2501193794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a speech to the closed meeting of the 
parliamentary majority in Tbilisi late on Monday [24 January], 
Georgian leader Eduard Shevarnadze called to tighten discipline 
and law enforcement in all tiers of management including 
parliament, well-informed sources told Interfax. 
  Shevardnadze demanded that parliamentary chief of staff 
Gamlet Chipashvili be sacked. He blamed the official for 
failing to include the main point about the country's 
territorial integrity in a memorandum published in Tbilisi on 
the results of Georgian-Abkhazian talks in Geneva. 

</TEXT>

