<H3> <TI>   Nazarbayev Interviewed by KAZAKHSTANSKAYA PRAVDA </TI></H3>
<H4>   Cited on Foreign Aid Package </H4>
<F P=102> PM2501110994 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 25 Jan 94 First 
Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2501110994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Vladimir Ardayev report: "World Community Grants </F>
Kazakhstan Over $1 Billion in Loans"] 
  [Text] Almaty -- A consultative conference of "donor" 
countries providing financial assistance to Kazakhstan has ended 
in Paris. It was decided that the republic will be allocated 
more than $1 billion this year to continue economic reform. 
  Kazakhstan's main "donors" were the IMF, the International 
Bank for Reconstruction and Development, Asian banks, and a 
number of states. For instance, $220 million was allocated by 
the Japanese Government. The European Bank for Reconstruction 
and Development has granted a 100 million-ECU [European currency 
unit] targeted loan for the financing of small and medium-sized 
enterprises. 
  The loans are being provided to Kazakhstan on favorable 
terms. For instance, the IMF loans are repayable over 17 years 
at an annual interest rate of 7 percent. Interest only will be 
paid for the first five years. 
  These facts were cited by Kazakhstani President Nursultan 
Nazarbayev in an interview with the newspaper KAZAKHSTANSKAYA 
PRAVDA. 

</TEXT>

