<H3> <TI>   ROK Grants $150,000 in Humanitarian Aid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2501193994 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 1500 GMT 
25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2501193994 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Kazakh </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vice President Yerik Asanbayev received the 
ambassador of the Republic of Korea to Kazakhstan at his request 
today. Under examination were prospects for furthering economic 
and cultural relations between our countries. Bilateral 
relations between the two countries are very effective, said 
Yerik Asanbayev. South Korean businessmen have began the 
production of TV sets in Almaty and fridges in Karaganda. 
  However, cooperation has to be boosted especially in the 
sphere of granting Kazakhstan credits. He [Asanbayev] expressed 
certainty that the South Korean side, which has promised to 
grant Kazakhstan with a credit of $350 million, will keep its 
word. The ambassador was thanked for pledging $150,000 in 
humanitarian aid that arrived from Seoul today. 
  The ambassador said that he will do everything so as to 
strengthen friendly ties between the two countries, facilitating 
economic ties, and attracting more investments from South Korea 
to Kazakhstan. 

