<H3> <TI>   Tajikistan's Rakhmanov Visits, Meets With Nazarbayev </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601120594 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network in Russian 
1000 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2601120594 </F>
<F P=104>  Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Imamali Rakhmanov, chairman of the Supreme Soviet of 
the Republic of Tajikistan, paid a short working visit to 
Almaty, yesterday, during which he had a tete-a-tete 
conversation with Kazakhstani President Nursultan Nazarbayev. 
  Nazarbayev and Rakhmanov exchanged views on the situation on 
the Tajik-Afghan border and on ways of reducing the (?tension) 
in this region in an atmosphere of mutual understanding. 
  Kazakhstan's president has evaluated in a positive manner 
the 
Tajik leadership's measures on adjusting the political dialogue 
with the forces of different political orientation aimed at 
seeking peace and concord on Tajik soil. While discussing 
regional issues, the two leaders focused on the necessity of new 
efforts to reinforce the effectiveness of the CIS peacekeeping 
forces. 
  The two leaders have confirmed the invariability of the 
course of both states toward strengthening the independence and 
expanding the traditional friendly relations between Kazakhstan 
and Tajikistan. 
  In a separate meeting, the delegatiions of Kazakhstan and 
Tajikistan discussed a wide range of economic issues, in 
particular on delivery of goods, ways of regulating mutual 
payments, and issues related to energy supply. 
  The government delegations of Kazakhstan and Tajikistan have 
confirmed the joint aspiration for the harmonious and balanced 
development of all-round relations. A number of economic 
intergovernmental and interdepartmental agreements were 
concluded at the end of the negotiations. 

</TEXT>

