<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Urges Duma To Approve Draft </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2501153994 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 25 Jan 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2501153994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Edict No. 173 of the Russian Federation president "On the </F>
Federal Assembly State Duma Draft Decree Declaring an Amnesty," 
dated Moscow, the Kremlin, 21 January 1994 and signed by Russian 
Federation President B. Yeltsin] 
  [Text] Taking into consideration the many appeals from 
private individuals and public organizations and requests from 
ther families of convicted and indicted individuals, guided by 
the principle of humanity, and in connection with the adoption 
of the Russian Federation Constitution, I decree that: 
  1. An act of amnesty should be proclaimed for certain 
categories of people convicted of crimes which do not represent 
an increased risk to the public. 
  2. The Federal Assembly State Duma draft decree declaring an 
amnesty should be approved so that the Russian Federation 
president can submit it for immediate scrutiny to the Federal 
Assembly State Duma in accordance with the procedure laid down 
in Paragraph "e" of Article 103 of the Russian Federation 
Constitution. 
  3. This Edict comes into force from the moment of its 
signing. 
  [Signed] President of the Russian Federation B. Yeltsin 
  [Dated] Moscow, the Kremlin, 21 January 1994 
  No. 173 

</TEXT>

