<H3> <TI>   Talks on Duma's Possible Move to Southeast Moscow </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK2501143094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 25 Jan 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK2501143094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["NG" report under the "In Brief" rubric: "Where Shall Duma </F>
Sit?"] 
  [Text] It has become known to NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA from a 
confidential source in the State Duma apparatus that most 
probably, the question of moving the lower chamber from the 
building of the former Council for Mutual Economic Assistance to 
a new location will be decided today. The same source has made 
it known that the most probable destination for the Duma is in 
southeast Moscow, in the building of Moscow's Academy of 
Management. Incidentally, this option was discussed during the 
meeting between President Yeltsin and Speaker Rybkin last week 
after Mr. Rybkin came in for criticism from the leaders of Duma 
factions for his excessive pliancy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

