<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Black Sea Fleet Officers Send Letter to Duma </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2501161394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1440 
GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2501161394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Ostanin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 25 Jan -- Officers of the Black Sea Fleet 
and their families are in a calamitous state, says a letter from 
the Coordinating Council of Officers' Assemblies to Russia's 
State Duma. The ITAR-TASS correspondent learned about the 
contents of the message in the Black Sea fleet press center 
today. 
  The officers voice their concern over allowance payments 
being two months in arrears, in view of increases in inflation. 
The document also draws attention to the fact that children of 
servicemen in the fleet cannot go to Ukraine's civilian higher 
education colleges, because they do not speak Ukrainian. 
  The Coordinating Council is also concerned, the letter says, 
that the proposal by the officers' assemblies for the Black Sea 
fleet to be granted the status of the Russian Federation fleet 
has not yet been considered at the state level. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

