<H3> <TI>   Military Exercises in Crimea Planned </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2501161794 Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA in Russian 25 Jan 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2501161794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "`Battle' in Crimea, Everything Up in </F>
Smoke"] 
  [Text] The increased tension in Crimea's sociopolitical 
life caused by Kiev's dissatisfaction with the results of the 
first round of the presidential election in Simferopol cannot, 
it appears, reduce the fighting spirit of the Ukrainian Armed 
Forces. From 24 through 28 January large-scale command-staff 
exercises are being conducted by Armed Forces units and commands 
on the territory of Odessa, Kherson, and Nikolayev Oblasts and 
in Crimea. 
  No doubt in this connection, in an interview with KIYEVSKIYE 
VEDOMOSTI Ukrainian Defense Minister General Radetskyy made the 
statement that "I would not like to have to liberate Crimea as 
the Americans liberated Kuwait." In response to this, Admiral 
Eduard Baltin, commander of the Black Sea Fleet, expressed doubt 
that the young, respected, and promising Ukrainian defense 
minister could become a General Schwarzkopf.... 

</TEXT>

