<H3> <TI>   Navy Chief Denies `Large-Scale' Maneuvers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2601123894 Kiev MOLOD UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 25 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU2601123894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev MOLOD UKRAYINY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report published under the rubric "Fact"] </F>
  [Text] The commander of Ukraine's Naval Forces, Vice 
Admiral Volodymyr Bezkorovaynyy, has refuted "Ostankino" 
assertions about alleged plans to conduct a large-scale training 
exercise of Ukrainian troops in the Crimea that might influence 
the course of presidential elections in the autonomous republic. 
As reported by the Press Service of Ukraine's Ministry of 
Defense, between 24 and 27 January, staff training will be held 
for all the armed forces without the involvement of troops or 
technology. The training will be supervised by the supreme 
commander, L. Kravchuk. 

</TEXT>

