<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party Urges Finance Minister To Resign </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK2501145094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 25 Jan 94 
p 3 </F>

<F P=103> MK2501145094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed NEGA report] </F>
  [Text] "The draft budget for 1994 presented to the Supreme 
Soviet in which expenditures coincide with revenues defies 
common sense and has no economic legitimacy." This is said in a 
statement by the Ukrainian Constitutional Democratic Party 
[UCDP] promulgated on 24 January. In the opinion of the 
Constitutional Democrats, the attempts to please international 
financial organizations will only further discredit Ukraine as a 
country "run by ignoramuses." The UCDP believes that no one in 
Ukraine has any illusions about the cabinet of ministers, but 
the performance by Finance Minister Hryhoriy Pyatachenko has 
transcended all permissible bounds. The UCDP has called for his 
immediate resignation. Meanwhile the Ukrainian Supreme Soviet 
will not return to the consideration of the budget until 27 
January. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

