<H3> <TI>   Brazauskas Sends Letter to Ukraine's Kravchuk </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2501203194 Tallinn BNS in English 1646 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2501203194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Jan 25, BNS -- Romualdas Ramoska, 
Lithuanian ambassador to Ukraine, presented on Monday [24 
January] a letter from Lithuanian President Algirdas Brazauskas 
to Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk. 
  Dainius Trinkunas, the Lithuanian president's foreign policy 
assistant, said the letter includes proposals on ways of 
improving economic relations, mutual settlements and exchange of 
Lithuanian and Ukrainian currencies. To attain these goals, 
Brazauskas proposed to create a joint Lithuanian-Ukrainian 
commercial bank, the presidential assistant said. 
  The Lithuanian president expressed hope that Kravchuk's 
forthcoming visit to Lithuania will stimulate further 
development of bilateral relations. 
  The Ukrainian president is scheduled to come to Lithuania 
Feb. 8-9. 

</TEXT>

