<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition To Urge No-Confidence Vote in Spring </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2501174494 Tallinn BNS in English 1414 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2501174494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Jan 25, BNS -- The board of Lithuanian 
Social Democratic Party [LSDP] expressed no confidence in the 
government and commissioned the parliamentary LSDP faction to 
start a constitutional process of taking a vote of no confidence 
in the Cabinet during the parliament's spring session. 
  MP Aloyzas Sakalas, chairman of both the party and the 
faction, told reporters Tuesday that the social democrats will 
ask other political forces to back their initiative because six 
members of the LSDP in the parliament will be unable to start 
the process alone. Sakalas said the parliament will consider 
their demand only if it is supported by at least 27 lawmakers. 
  In a statement released last weekend, the social democrats 
mainly criticize the government's refusal to set a more 
favorable exchange proportion for people's savings during the 
introduction of national currency, as well as to draw a distinct 
line between legally and illegally acquired money. 
  The LSDP said the Cabinet does not observe the government 
program that was approved by the parliament, has not worked out 
a program for industry reconstruction and failed to draft an 
investment program. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

