<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fedorov Turns Down Finance Minister Post </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601091294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0852 
GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2601091294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Talalayev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 26 January -- Boris Fedorov is leaving the 
post of finance minister. 
  His press secretary Olga Leonova told ITAR-TASS that at a 
meeting with Russian President Boris Yeltsin this morning, Boris 
Fedorov rejected the proposal to take the post of finance 
minister in the reformed government on the conditions offered to 
him. 
  At the same time, according to the press secretary, 
conditions put forward by Boris Fedorov were not accepted. 
  ITAR-TASS has learned that Boris Fedorov is preparing a 
statement for the press. 

</TEXT>

