<H3> <TI>   Volkogonov To Continue To Advise Yeltsin on Security </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2501152994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1410 
GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2501152994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Veronika Romanenkova] </F>
  [Excerpt] Moscow, 25 Jan (ITAR-TASS) -- Dmitriy Volkogonov, 
who yesterday was relieved by presidential decree of the duties 
of defense and security advisor to the Russian president, 
proposes to continue to carry out his previous functions but on 
a "freelance" and unsalaried basis. As a deputy of the State 
Duma, he may not simultaneously be in state service, 
Colonel-General Volkogonov told the ITAR-TASS correspondent 
today. 
  "In consultation with Boris Yeltsin and Yegor Gaydar, we 
decided that I should stay in the Duma, because the "Russia's 
Choice" group I belong to is relatively small," Dmitriy 
Volkogonov said. In addition, he will continue work in the 
three presidential commissions researching into cases of missing 
foreign citizens and of Russian Federation citizens who 
disappeared in unexplained circumstances outside the former 
USSR, and into the use of and declassification of the 
presidential archive. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

