<H3> <TI>   Deputy Health Ministers Resign </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601091994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0844 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2601091994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow January 26 TASS -- "Two Russian deputy 
ministers of public health and medical industry, who tendered 
their resignation, said they had taken this step out of their 
own free will. Nothing is said in their applications that they 
are resigning because they do not agree with the policy pursued 
by heads of the ministry," Public Health Minister Eduard 
Nechayev told ITAR-TASS, commenting on the resignation of First 
Deputy Minister Aleksey Moskvichev and Deputy Minister Vladimir 
Starodubov. 
  New candidates to the posts have already been found, a 
ministry spokesman told ITAR-TASS. They are doctors of medicine 
and, in the opinion of senior officials, they are skilled 
professionals. According to the same source, the two resigning 
deputy ministers will quickly find employment for themselves. 
Starodubov will probably continue to work at the medical 
institute. He combined that job with working as deputy minister. 

</TEXT>

