<H3> <TI>   Chernomyrdin Denies Discussing Cabinet With Yeltsin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401190994 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1800 GMT 
24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2401190994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Viktor Chernomyrdin has said to INTERFAX that the 
main topic of his meeting with Boris Yeltsin today was the 
budget for the fourth quarter of this year. Chernomyrdin 
arrived in Orel to take part in a meeting of oblast leaders from 
Central Russia. He said that he and Yeltsin did not talk about 
the new cabinet. 
  Speaking about the candidacy of Boris Fedorov for the post 
of 
finance minister, Viktor Chernomyrdin said that he had spoken to 
him about it on both Sunday [23 Janaury] and Monday. During 
these conversations he asked Fedorov to finally decide whether 
he was going to join the government or not. 

