<H3> <TI>   Shokhin Views New Appointments in Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401202594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1837 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2401202594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] By order of Viktor Chernomyrdin, the Economics 
Minister Aleksandr Shokhin, as a member of the government's 
presidium, is temporarily in charge of the ministry for 
cooperation with the CIS states, Shokhin himself told 
journalists on Monday. 
  According to Shokhin, "Vladimir Mashitz will be responsible 
for the economic affairs in the ministry." As for Konstantin 
Zatulin, a member of the PRES [Party of Russian Unity and 
Accord] faction in the State Duma, of which Shokhin is a member) 
[no open parentheses as received], he is the head of the Duma's 
Committee for CIS Affairs and Ties with Compatriots. Shokhin 
has no information about the nomination of Zatulin as the 
minister for cooperation with the CIS states. 
  As it was reported earlier, Shokhin was also appointed the 
Economics Minister. 
  Shokhin hopes that the Economics Ministry will have "real 
authorities, although this does not mean the revival of GOSPLAN 
(the State Planning Committee)." Shokhin also expressed hope 
for the real interaction with the Finance Ministry reminding 
that in the past the two ministries had different approaches to 
the resolution of economic problems and public discussions took 
place which the new economics minister hopes to avoid in the 
future. 

</TEXT>

