<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Health Minister Appointment Triggers Resignations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2501095194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0936 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2501095194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anna Bakina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 25 TASS -- Two high officials of the 
Russian Ministry of Health -- First Deputy Minister Aleksey 
Moskvichev and Deputy Minister Vladimir Starodubov -- sent in 
their resignations after the appointment of Eduard Nechayev as 
health minister had been endorsed. ITAR-TASS learned this from 
a well-informed source. The source said there is a conflict 
between deputy ministers and Nechayev, so Moskvichev and 
Starodubov deemed it impossible to work under his direction. 
Nechayev has signed the resignations which are now considered 
by the government. 
  New candidatures to fill the posts have already been found, 
ITAR-TASS was told. 

</TEXT>

